metadata.name: Singapore Landmarks
metadata.description:
Singapore is a true wonder of Southeast Asia, with its blend of Asian and European cultures. There is a vibrant history and diverse ethnic quarters to discover, along with many family-friendly attractions and lovely public spaces that make exploring this slightly futuristic city worthwhile. Graceful colonial buildings co-exist alongside centuries-old street markets and modern high-rises.

Animated art combined beautiful scenery with Singapore icon such as Singapore Flyer, Buddha Tooth Relic Temple, ArtScience Museum, Garden by the Bay Supertree Grove and Marina Bay Sands.

Edition 1/1
